title: 10 Loudest College Football Stadiums
name: 10 Loudest College Football Stadiums
description:
A Map by Vpat89

This map will contain the ten loudest college football stadiums across the country.

properties.name: Beaver Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89University Park, PennsylvaniaBeaver stadium home to the Penn State Nittany Lions football team. Penn State known for its "white outs" and their legendary coach Joe Paterno

properties.name: Ben Hill Griffin Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89Gainesville, FLBen Hill Grffin Stadium is the home to the University of Florida football team. Ben Hill Griffin Stadium holds 89,000. Florida football is known for it\'s consistent success in football

properties.name: Camp Randall Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89Camp Randall Stadium is the home to the University of Wisconsin football team. Camp Randall Stadium seats 81,318.

properties.name: Clemson Memorial Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89clemson,scThis is Clemson Memorial Stadium home to the Clemson Tigers. The stadium seats 86,000 people. Clemson football known for its rich tradition and fans.

properties.name: Jordan-Hare Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89Auburn, ALJordan-Hare Stadium home to the Auburn University football team. The stadium seats 86,000.

properties.name: Kyle Field
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89College Station, TXKyle Field is the home to the Texas A & M football team. Kyle field seats 82,600.

properties.name: Lane Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89Blacksburg, VALane Stadium is home to the Virgnia Tech Hokies football team. Lane Stadium seats 65,513. Lane Stadium is the "smallest largest stadium".

properties.name: Neyland Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89Knoxville TNNeyland stadium home to the Tennessee Volunteers football team. Neyland Stadium can seat 107,000. The Tennessee football team has rich tradition and winning history

properties.name: Ohio Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89Columbus, OhioOhio Stadium is home to the Ohio State University football team located in Columbus Ohio. The stadium seats 101,568. Ohio Stadium is known for it\'s horseshoe shape.

properties.name: Tiger Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Vpat89Baton Rouge, LATiger Stadium is home to the Louisana State University football team. Tiger stadium seats 92,000. Tiger stadium holds the record for 2nd loudest outdoor stadium.
